The paper is primarily focused on the computational complexity of finding approximate Nash equilibria in bimatrix games, which is a central topic in game theory (cs.GT). The paper also uses techniques from data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.AI) to design and analyze querying algorithms. Additionally, the paper discusses lower bounds on the query complexity of randomized algorithms, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT).
